Key Match Events: Benin manages to come from behind against Libya to take three key points in the CAF qualifiers.
Olaitan converts the penalty and gives his country the partial comeback goal.
Mounié equalizes the score with a great volley after a cross from the left flank.
Al Badri converts the penalty kick and scores the first goal of the match for Libya.
Al Woheshi, Libya's goalkeeper, made several good saves.
Pre-Game Insights: Steve Mounié is the player to watch for Benin, having played 51 games for his national team, scoring 17 goals and providing 3 assists.
Ahmed Elmsmari is the most interesting player of the Libyan national team, currently 18 years old and playing for FC Barcelona B.
The match between Benin vs Libya on matchday 2 of the African qualifiers will be played at the Stade Félix Houphouët Boigny located in Abidjan, Ivory Coast, with a capacity of 45,000 spectators.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The approximate temperature at the Stade Félix Houphouët Boigny was around 82 degrees Fahrenheit.
Libya had to play its matches outside its country for almost 7 years due to war and conflict.
Benin lost its first match against Nigeria with a final score of 3-0.
